13 S.Ct. 260

BROWN
v.
MARION NAT. BANK OF LEBANON.

No. 1,123.

December 19, 1892.

1

T. L. Burnett and H. M. Lane, (Rives & Spalding, on the brief,) for plaintiff in error.

2

W. J. Lisle, for defendant in error.

3

THE CHIEF JUSTICE.

4

The writ of error is dismissed, upon the authority of Meagher v. Manufacturing Co., 145 U. S. 608, 12 Sup. Ct. Rep. 876; Rice v. Sanger, 144 U. S. 197, 12 Sup. Ct. Rep. 664; Johnson v. Keith, 117 U. S. 199, 6 Sup. Ct. Rep. 669.
